Problems with arrays:
--------------------
 -> Fixed size
 -> It cant dynamically grow.(when add elements it cant grow dynamically.)
 -> Difficult to add or remove elements.

All these issues are resolved in collections.
------------------------------------------------------------

Java Collection:
----------------
    It is framework(set of classes and interfaces), used to store, manage and manipulate group of objects dynamically.

 Store:
 ------
    List<String> li = new ArrayList<>();
    li.add("Apple");
    li.add("Mango");
    li.add("Banana");  

manage:
  Adding an element in a particular position.
  Updting an element in a position.
  Remove an element.
  li.set(3, "Grape") // adding an element in particular position
  li.set(0, "Jackfruit"); // Apple will be replaced with jackfruit.
  li.remove("Banana");

  Manipulte Data:
     Searching - li.contains("Mango")
     Sorting -  Collections.sort(li); 


